body:
Consider the following SV design:

```verilog
module top;
	task test_task;
	begin
		fork
		begin
			$display("Process #1");
			#20
			$display ("Process #1 -- completes");
		end

		begin
			// Here's a timeout task.  It should only complete if
			// something in process #1 fails to complete.  As such,
			// it operates as a failsafe.
			$display("Process #2");
			#200
			$display("Process #2 -- completes");
		end

		join_any;
		disable fork;

		$display("Test task completes");
	end endtask

	initial	test_task;
endmodule
```

This function uses fork to create two subtasks: A primary and a secondary timeout.  In the original example this was drawn from, the primary depended on some external events, and so the secondary was a fail-safe in case those events didn't happen.  As soon as the first of the two tasks finishes, the design kills the other task and then outputs an error if the failsafe completed.

I am building this test design using: `iverilog -g2012 ivtestcase.sv`, and then running it via `./a.out`.  When I do so, this design then fails with the message, `vvp: vthread.cc:3795: bool of_JOIN_DETACH(vthread_t, vvp_code_t): assertion 'thr->task_func_children.empty()' failed`.

Any potential workarounds would also be appreciated.

Dan

